# MCP and plugin routing

Development is **100% in Cursor**. Prefer **checked-in `scripts/*.sh`** for build/run/test
(the deterministic local loop). Use MCPs to augment — not replace — those scripts.

## Enabled MCP servers (current)

| Server ID | Name | Use for |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `user-xcodebuildmcp` | xcodebuildmcp | Apple platform build/test/run via MCP tools (see scope below) |
| `user-context7` | context7 | Library/SDK/CLI docs (`resolve-library-id` → `query-docs`) |
| `plugin-chrome-devtools-mcp-chrome-devtools` | chrome-devtools | Website verification (`navigate_page`, `take_snapshot`, `take_screenshot`, …) |
| `cursor-ide-browser` | cursor-ide-browser | In-IDE browser tab (`browser_navigate`, `browser_snapshot`, …) |
| `plugin-huggingface-skills-huggingface-skills` | huggingface-skills | Hub model/dataset/paper lookup (`hub_repo_search`, `hub_repo_details`, …) |
| `cursor-app-control` | cursor-app-control | Cursor IDE control (`open_resource`, `move_agent_to_root`, `rename_chat`, …) |

Invoke MCP tools with **`CallMcpTool`** (read each tool's JSON descriptor under the MCP
filesystem first). Use the **Shell** tool for terminal commands — not a separate Bash tool.

## XcodeBuildMCP (`user-xcodebuildmcp`)

Read the **`xcodebuildmcp`** skill (`SKILL.md`) before first use.

**Enabled workflows** (see repo [`.xcodebuildmcp/config.yaml`](mdc:.xcodebuildmcp/config.yaml)):
`simulator`, `macos`, `device`, `debugging`, `ui-automation`, `project-discovery`.
Reload the MCP server after editing that file (Cursor → Settings → MCP → xcodebuildmcp → Restart).

Tools include `session_show_defaults`, `session_use_defaults_profile`, `build_sim`,
`test_sim`, `build_macos`, `build_run_macos`, `test_macos`, `test_device`, `debug_attach_sim`,
`snapshot_ui`, `list_devices`, etc. Extra workflows (coverage, xcode-ide, …) can be added to
`enabledWorkflows` — see https://xcodebuildmcp.com/docs/configuration

**Session discipline (required):**

1. Call `session_show_defaults` before the first build/run/test in a session.
2. Switch profiles with `session_use_defaults_profile`: `ios-sim` (Tier-A Simulator),
   `macos` (`QwenVoice`), `ios-device` (Tier-B — set `deviceId` via `session_set_defaults`).
3. Use `discover_projs` only when defaults are missing or wrong — never speculatively.
4. Prefer combined tools (`build_run_sim`, `build_run_macos`) over separate build + launch chains.

**Vocello routing:**

- **macOS app (`QwenVoice` scheme):** `./scripts/build.sh` remains primary; MCP
  `build_run_macos` / `test_macos` are OK for quick checks (`session_use_defaults_profile: macos`).
- **Tier-A iOS fake-backend tests (`VocelloiOS`, `QVOICE_FAKE_ENGINE=1`):** MCP simulator
  tools (`test_sim`, `build_run_sim`, `snapshot_ui`) OK on the Simulator and in CI
  (profile `ios-sim`).
- **Tier-B real-engine iOS (MLX/Metal/generation/download):** prefer `scripts/ios_device.sh`
  on a paired iPhone. MCP `device` tools are optional helpers (profile `ios-device` + runtime
  `deviceId`) — never the Simulator or simulator UI tools.

## Context7 (`user-context7`)

For GRDB, SwiftHuggingFace, React, Vite, and any non-Apple library docs — even when you
think you know the API. Do **not** use for refactoring, business logic, or general CS.

Steps: `resolve-library-id` → pick best `/org/project` match → `query-docs` with the full
question. User rule: [`.cursor/rules/context7.mdc`](mdc:.cursor/rules/context7.mdc) (if
present at user level, same policy applies).

## Browser verification (website)

For `website/`: read `website/PRODUCT.md` + `website/DESIGN.md`, then either:

- **`chrome-devtools`** MCP — full DevTools (network, performance, Lighthouse), or
- **`cursor-ide-browser`** MCP — lightweight in-IDE tab automation.

Run `npm --prefix website run dev|preview` via Shell first.

## Hugging Face (`plugin-huggingface-skills-huggingface-skills`)

For model revision lookup, dataset metadata, and hub search. The **`hf` CLI** and Hugging
Face skills remain valid for downloads and local model management.

## Cursor app control (`cursor-app-control`)

Use sparingly: `open_resource` to reveal files/terminals/URLs in Glass, `rename_chat` for
conversation titles, `move_agent_to_root` after worktree switches. Do **not** use for
build/test automation.

## Axiom plugin (auditors + CLI)

Subagents via the **Task** tool (`crash-analyzer`, `build-fixer`, `test-runner`,
`concurrency-auditor`, …) or `/axiom:audit <domain>`. Binaries (`xcsym`, `xcprof`, `xclog`)
ship in the Axiom plugin. **Do not** drive app UI through Axiom `xcui` / `simulator-tester` for real-engine iOS work** — use deterministic XCUITest + `scripts/*.sh`.

## UI review baselines (vision diff)

After `scripts/macos_test.sh review` or `scripts/ios_device.sh review`, compare captures
vs `docs/*-review-baselines/` using the **`screenshot-validator`** Axiom subagent
(`/axiom:audit screenshots`) or a manual visual pass. The retired `zai-mcp-server`
`ui_diff_check` tool is no longer available.

## Retired / off-limits

- Agent/computer-use screen driving — gone; see [`testing-runbook.md`](mdc:docs/reference/testing-runbook.md).
- **`plugin-xcodebuildmcp-sentry`** — removed; use `user-xcodebuildmcp`.
- Real-engine iOS on Simulator — off-limits (§7 in root [`AGENTS.md`](mdc:AGENTS.md)).
